title: Cannot see images in labeled-data folder after frame extraction (while inside labeling GUI)
body:
Thanks for opening this issue, and thanks for using DeepLabCut (we hope you are enjoying it ;). Please fill out the template completely, including the full "TRACEBACK" and input code that you ran to hit this error. **Describe the bug** Hello I am a little new to deeplabcut. First of all, thank you very much for your work. I have a problem when viewing frames. I cannot extract the frames because pictures(jpg) are not visible when I go into the related file. However when I enter the same file from the desktop, I see the files are there. **Desktop (please complete the following information about your system):** - OS: [e.g. Windows10 Home 19042.685] - DeepLabCut Version [2.1.9] - DeepLabCut mode: single animal tracking, - Browser, if applicable [chrome,] **To Reproduce** Steps to reproduce the behavior, i.e.: 1. Go to '...' 2. Click on '....' 3. Scroll down to '....' 4. the input code you used (i.e. `deeplabcut.train_network( .... )`) 4. See error:

**Expected behavior** When I want to extract the necessary frames from the file, I expect the jpgs to come instead of the empty folder. **Screenshots** Here are the steps that i followed. ![aşama 1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/70771176/103692547-f648d380-4fa8-11eb-82f1-7f4020a6055c.png) ![aşama 2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/70771176/103692564-fb0d8780-4fa8-11eb-8348-a55f6ac2be68.png) After this stage, a message appears as: Extracting frames based on kmeans ... Kmeans-quantization based extracting of frames from 0.0 seconds to 5.0 seconds. Extracting and downsampling... 150 frames from the video. 150it [00:01, 147.33it/s] Kmeans clustering ... (this might take a while) C:\Users\OkanT\anaconda3\envs\DLC-CPU\lib\site-packages\sklearn\cluster\_kmeans.py:888: UserWarning: MiniBatchKMeans is known to have a memory leak on Windows with MKL, when there are less chunks than available threads. You can prevent it by setting batch_size >= 1024 or by setting the environment variable OMP_NUM_THREADS=1 f"MiniBatchKMeans is known to have a memory leak on " Frames were successfully extracted, for the videos of interest. You can now label the frames using the function 'label_frames' (if you extracted enough frames for all videos). ![aşama 3](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/70771176/103692812-65262c80-4fa9-11eb-8b2f-25f53bbca0cb.png) ![aşama 4](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/70771176/103692826-68211d00-4fa9-11eb-9836-7a46cf79a6dc.png) **Additional context** Add any other context about the problem here.
